The article is a transcript of remarks made by Vice President Mike Pence at the Philadelphia Fraternal Order of Police Lodge #5. Pence expressed his support for law enforcement officers and condemned the efforts to defund the police. He highlighted the bravery and sacrifices of police officers and praised their role in maintaining public safety. Pence also discussed the need to support both law enforcement and communities, emphasizing that they are not mutually exclusive. He mentioned the importance of justice being served in cases like the death of George Floyd, but also criticized the rioting and looting that followed. Pence reassured law enforcement officers that they are admired and appreciated by the American people, and he pledged the administration's continued support for the police.